<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id77b925e6-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s459i–9"><num value="459i–9">§ 459i–9.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There are authorized to be appropriated not to exceed $28,500,000 for the acquisition of lands and interests in lands and not to exceed $27,840,000 for development of the seashore.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id77b925e7-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/92/536/s10">Pub. L. 92–536, § 10</ref>, <date date="1972-10-23">Oct. 23, 1972</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/86/1068">86 Stat. 1068</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/95/625/tII/s201/3">Pub. L. 95–625, title II, § 201(3)</ref>, <date date="1978-11-10">Nov. 10, 1978</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/92/3473">92 Stat. 3473</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
